-- AMR shares rally, says cash position bolstered
-- 
-- Thu Sep 17, 2009 9:58am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/09/17/us-beforethebell-amr-sb-idUSTRE58G2CN20090917

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of AMR Corp, the parent company of American Airlines, rose 15.2 percent to $8.47 in premarket trading on Thursday, after the company said it had bolstered its liquidity and planned to take steps that include buying new planes in a bid to return to profitability. 

 (Reporting by  Ryan Vlastelica ; Editing by Theodore d'Afflisio)